title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.3 HEALTH COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT

description.narrative: By 2024, families and communities are equipped with knowledge and actively demand quality health services.(UNSDCF Output 1.3), which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024: Significantly more girls, boys, adolescents and women, especially those who are marginalized and/or living in humanitarian conditions, have access to and utilize evidence-based, high-impact quality maternal, neonatal, child, adolescent health, and HIV interventions.
